	I've been researching Quantum Cryptorgraphy (Benett, Brassard, Ekert, et el.),
and is it possible by using photon interferometry to have multi-node fiber optic cable
for transmission.  That is, theoretically the distance for key transmission will _not_
be limited as it would be in the traditional photon polarization scheme.
